.TH "device_get_mac_address" 9 "device_get_mac_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_get_mac_address \- Get the MAC for a given device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" device_get_mac_address
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "char *addr "  ","
.BI "int alen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Pointer to the device
.IP "addr" 12
Address of buffer to store the MAC in
.IP "alen" 12
Length of the buffer pointed to by addr, should be ETH_ALEN
